op=20>1</a><a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showMessageRange?topicID=512.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showMessageRange?topicID=512.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a> <b>4</b>  </td><td align=right> <br> <a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showPrevMessage?topicID=512.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showNextMessage?topicID=512.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top bgcolor=32323c class=headings><font color=#ffffff>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=32323c class=headings><font color=#ffffff>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umissxeni.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MissXeni</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/30/01 9:57:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=512.topic&index=61>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: weee movie</span><hr size=1> I had to post.  With 103 degree fever, I sat at my computer and by the side of Fionna, our lvl 60 cleric for 26 hours.  It started as a way to support my guild mate who at level 60 would be our first cleric with the rez stick and it ended in defending her from basic in-game terrorists.<br>
<br>
At the side of Matahari who took down Naggy, Fionna encouraged, buffed, healed and rezzed.  At the side of Matahari, Fionna fought and killed Ragefire... not on the condition she could take their camp over when they were done... she did it just because she wanted a fellow cleric to have their epic.  At the side of Matahari, Fionna made a decision to continue the camp, surrounded by friends, guild mates, allies and strangers that wanted to help her get her epic as well.<br>
<br>
Some people view it as obssessive.. it's just a game... it doesn't really figure into anyone's real life.  Ask the young girl's family from Karana server who lost her battle with cancer.  Completely isolated from human contact during her battle with leukemia, EQ was her source of communication and inspiration.  If for one moment, you attach the name Fionna to that girl, you have a hell of a different story line for this event. The impact of what Landslide did not only remains to be the singular most abhorent behavior I have personally witnessed in this game by a player to a player, the fact that it was a guild mounted terrorist act by those too weak to deal with accepted modes of operation BEGS for appropriate action by server GMs, guilds that are a decent and players that won't allow this lack of respect to exist.<br>
<br>
I'm not saying to take pity on people.... but as much as it is a game, as much as it 'really doesn't matter in real life' if Fionna or any other cleric gets their epic, there are HUMANS behind every PC roaming character in Norrath.<br>
<br>
As an officer of Immortal Mercy, I talked with Fenriz (guild leader of Landslide) for at least an hour when they first arrived to invade our camp.  At the time, there were over 20 people in the Lair that were there to help Fionna attain her last piece for her epic only three of which were in IM.  Fenriz named guild name after guild name of those that were in the zone and to each one I responded, &quot;They are here helping us too.&quot;  Matahari, Vision, Stone Dogs, Sphere of Transcendence, Allied Giants, Dragons of Mist, Tides of Valor, Seven Eyes and others were all present on behalf of Fionna's diligent camp.  <br>
<br>
What followed was shocking.  Landslide pet casters, planted their pets on the RF spawn point while Landslide guild members piled onto the same spot in an effort to prevent Fionna from turning in her Shimmering Pearl.  It was no longer about their cleric getting the Ragefire spawn first... it became an effort to prohibit Fionna from even approaching Ragefire when he spawned.<br>
<br>
You can read the rest of the details in Sorcha's post on the first page of this thread.<br>
<br>
Landslide self admittedly can not take down Naggy.  They have now made a reputation for themselves on countless occasions of KSing various high level camps; of training guilds in an effort to take over a camp (Venril Sathir); KSing mobs by training creatures to kill groups mid-way through a fight so they could finish off the mob, loot it and flee before the original group made it back to the zone (Lodizal) all because they were not going to waste their time on a camp when another guild will &quot;camp it for them&quot; and Lanslide can come in at spawn time and KS the mob.<br>
<br>
Landslide is the Landfill of Norrath.  I'm anxious for the day that enough guilds and people petition Landslide's behavior that Verant has no alternative but to ban each Landslide player from eq.  In this instance, you deserve to be judged by the company you keep.<br>
