<br>
We've had a lot of people help us camp Ragefire.  Until recently we didn't have the &quot;low mains + alt&quot; support to do Nagafen.  Our mains were too high, our alts were too low.  Like other guilds on the server, we had to depend on our relationship with the other guilds.<br>
<br>
There are a handful of players, and, it seems, a handful of guilds who continue to demonstrate that they have no interest in working as a community.  Again and again the rules of the game are confused with the rules of polite society.  The <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>excuse</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> given for doing things to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  people</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
<br>
There are people behind the characters in this &quot;game.&quot;  They laugh, they cry, they enjoy each other's company.  They get happy, they get angry, and sometimes they get frustrated enough to throw punches at each other.<br>
<br>
I'm not interested in using the game as a tool to take joy away from other people.  It's disgusting that other people are.<br>
<br>
Palimax Sceleris<br>
Guildleader Vision<br>
