<br>
The difference is: you don't choose the colour of your skin, but you do choose who you associate with.  Because you made that choice, the actions of your associates rub off on you.  Not 100% - people who were not there are obviously not directly responsible.  But... you could deguild.  Or you could try to convince your guild to make amends and hence clear the air... help Fionna camp Rage as someone suggested.<br>
<br>
If you don't take action, you are tacitly approving of the actions of your associates.<br>
<br>
You may feel free to ignore me here, but it is the way the real world works - best learn this lesson here in a game than learn it the hard way in RL where it counts :-)<br>
<br>
Glencannon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ukarmonshadowstalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karmon Shadowstalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/9/01 10:33:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=512.topic&index=71>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I am sad..</span><hr size=1> When I see someone acting like an ass, I'll do a /guildstatus. <br>
